cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use EvalSurfer in your work, please cite it as below."
title: "EvalSurfer: A skill-first, agent-native evaluation protocol for AI applications"
abstract: >-
  EvalSurfer is a skill-first, agent-native evaluation protocol for AI
  applications. A portable SKILL.md lets coding agents act as the judge, while a
  deterministic, zero-dependency Python layer plans scope, validates reports,
  auto-scores operational SLOs, explains failures, tracks regressions,
  calibrates judges, and gates releases — with no LLM API calls in the core.
